1d:["$","div",null,{"className":"markdown-container","children":[["$","h1","h1-0",{"children":"History of Automation: Part 3"}],"\n",["$","h2","h2-0",{"children":"The Digital & AI Era (1990 – 2026)"}],"\n",["$","p","p-0",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Scope"}],": The standardization of software, the deep learning revolution, modern autonomous vehicles, and the rise of Agentic AI."]}],"\n",["$","hr","hr-0",{}],"\n",["$","h2","h2-1",{"children":"1. Standardization and Connectivity (1990 - 2010)"}],"\n",["$","h3","h3-0",{"children":"1993: IEC 61131-3 Standard (PLC Programming)"}],"\n",["$","p","p-1",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Event"}],": The International Electrotechnical Commission publishes the IEC 61131-3 standard.",["$","br","br-0",{}],"\n",["$","strong","strong-1",{"children":"Scope"}],": Unifies PLC programming into standard languages (Ladder logic, Structured text, Function block diagram).",["$","br","br-1",{}],"\n",["$","strong","strong-2",{"children":"Impact"}],": Drives global vendor interoperability and massively lowers the barrier to training new automation engineers."]}],"\n",["$","h3","h3-1",{"children":"2004–2005: The DARPA Grand Challenges"}],"\n",["$","p","p-2",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Event"}],": DARPA hosts competitions challenging teams to build fully autonomous vehicles capable of navigating a 150-mile off-road course in the Mojave Desert.\n",["$","strong","strong-1",{"children":"Significance"}],": In 2004, no vehicle completed the course. In 2005, five vehicles successfully finished (led by Stanford's \"Stanley\").\n",["$","strong","strong-2",{"children":"Impact"}],": This catalyzed the modern autonomous vehicle (AV) industry, proving that LiDAR, computer vision, and probabilistic robotics could work outside controlled environments. It led directly to the founding of Waymo."]}],"\n",["$","h3","h3-2",{"children":"2005: OPC UA Standard Released"}],"\n",["$","p","p-3",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Event"}],": Release of the Object Linking and Embedding (OLE) for Process Control Unified Architecture.",["$","br","br-0",{}],"\n",["$","strong","strong-1",{"children":"Purpose"}],": Standardize industrial data exchange with semantic meaning (not just raw values).",["$","br","br-1",{}],"\n",["$","strong","strong-2",{"children":"Impact"}],": Provides the critical communication backbone for Industry 4.0, bridging operational technology (OT) and information technology (IT)."]}],"\n",["$","h3","h3-3",{"children":"2007: Release of ROS (Robot Operating System)"}],"\n",["$","p","p-4",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Event"}],": Stanford AI Lab and Willow Garage release ROS.",["$","br","br-0",{}],"\n",["$","strong","strong-1",{"children":"Significance"}],": Provides a standard, open-source middleware for robotics (publish/subscribe messaging, hardware abstraction).",["$","br","br-1",{}],"\n",["$","strong","strong-2",{"children":"Impact"}],": Eliminates the need to \"reinvent the wheel\" for every new robot; democratizes robotics research globally."]}],"\n",["$","hr","hr-1",{}],"\n",["$","h2","h2-2",{"children":"2. The Deep Learning Revolution (2012 - 2020)"}],"\n",["$","h3","h3-4",{"children":"2012: AlexNet & The Deep Learning Boom"}],"\n",["$","p","p-5",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Event"}],": A Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) called AlexNet destroys the competition in the ImageNet challenge, proving the superiority of deep learning over classical computer vision.\n",["$","strong","strong-1",{"children":"Impact on Automation"}],": Transitioned robotic perception from brittle, hand-coded feature extraction to robust, learned representations. Allowed robots to \"see\" and classify objects in messy, unstructured environments like warehouses and homes."]}],"\n","$L26","\n","$L27","\n","$L28","\n","$L29","\n","$L2a","\n","$L2b","\n","$L2c","\n","$L2d","\n","$L2e","\n","$L2f","\n","$L30","\n","$L31","\n","$L32","\n","$L33","\n","$L34","\n","$L35"]}]
26:["$","h3","h3-5",{"children":"2014: Emergence of RPA (Robotic Process Automation)"}]
27:["$","p","p-6",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Event"}],": Coining of the term RPA and rapid growth of companies like UiPath and Blue Prism.",["$","br","br-0",{}],"\n",["$","strong","strong-1",{"children":"Technology"}],": Software bots that mimic human UI interactions (clicks, typing) to automate repetitive clerical tasks.",["$","br","br-1",{}],"\n",["$","strong","strong-2",{"children":"Impact"}],": Automation aggressively expands beyond physical factories into the corporate back-office (finance, HR, data entry)."]}]
28:["$","h3","h3-6",{"children":"2016-2018: Deep Reinforcement Learning Successes"}]
29:["$","p","p-7",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Event"}],": DeepMind's AlphaGo defeats Lee Sedol (2016); OpenAI Five defeats human pros in Dota 2 (2018).",["$","br","br-0",{}],"\n",["$","strong","strong-1",{"children":"Automation Parallel"}],": OpenAI demonstrates a robot hand solving a Rubik's cube single-handed (2019) using Domain Randomization and reinforcement learning.",["$","br","br-1",{}],"\n",["$","strong","strong-2",{"children":"Significance"}],": Proves that AI can discover complex physical control policies entirely through simulation (Sim2Real transfer)."]}]
2a:["$","hr","hr-2",{}]
2b:["$","h2","h2-3",{"children":"3. The Era of Foundation Models (2022 - 2026)"}]
2c:["$","h3","h3-7",{"children":"2023: Robotics Transformers (RT-1 & RT-2)"}]
2d:["$","p","p-8",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Event"}],": Google DeepMind releases Vision-Language-Action (VLA) models.",["$","br","br-0",{}],"\n",["$","strong","strong-1",{"children":"Significance"}],": Instead of training a small model for one specific task, a massive LLM backbone is fine-tuned to output physical robot actions.",["$","br","br-1",{}],"\n",["$","strong","strong-2",{"children":"Impact"}],": Robots demonstrate \"emergent reasoning\"—e.g., asked to \"pick up the extinct animal,\" the robot correctly identifies and picks up a plastic dinosaur without explicit programming."]}]
2e:["$","h3","h3-8",{"children":"2024: Open-Source Robotics Stacks & Octo"}]
2f:["$","p","p-9",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Event"}],": Release of the Open X-Embodiment dataset and the open-source Octo model.",["$","br","br-0",{}],"\n",["$","strong","strong-1",{"children":"Significance"}],": 22 different robot types across 20 institutions share training data. A single model (Octo) is trained to control all of them.",["$","br","br-1",{}],"\n",["$","strong","strong-2",{"children":"Impact"}],": Proves that scaling laws apply to physical automation just as they do to language models."]}]
30:["$","h3","h3-9",{"children":"2025: The Humanoid Pilot Phase"}]
31:["$","p","p-10",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Event"}],": Humanoid robots (Tesla Optimus, Figure 02, Agility Digit) transition from R&D labs to commercial pilot deployments in automotive factories and warehouses.",["$","br","br-0",{}],"\n",["$","strong","strong-1",{"children":"Significance"}],": The first viable general-purpose robotic form factor, capable of utilizing environments designed exclusively for humans."]}]
32:["$","h3","h3-10",{"children":"2026: Agentic AI Replaces RPA"}]
33:["$","p","p-11",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Event"}],": The mainstream deployment of Computer-Use Agents (e.g., Anthropic Claude Computer Use, OpenAI Operator).",["$","br","br-0",{}],"\n",["$","strong","strong-1",{"children":"Significance"}],": Traditional deterministic RPA scripts are replaced by autonomous AI agents that perceive screens, reason about goals, and execute actions dynamically, recovering from UI changes automatically."]}]
34:["$","hr","hr-3",{}]
